<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 30 at 7:56PM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>Areas of fog, locally dense, will continue this evening into the
overnight. Visibilities will generally run 1/2 to 1 mile, with
some areas down to 1/4 mile or less.
If driving, be prepared for changeable and suddenly reduced
visibilities. Proceed with extra caution, drive slowly and allow
for extra space between vehicles. Also, use low beam headlights.</description>
